    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Tour Sketches</title>
        <published>2021-02-25T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2021-02-25T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://blog.jimmac.eu/posts/tour-sketches/"/>
        <id>https://blog.jimmac.eu/posts/tour-sketches/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://blog.jimmac.eu/posts/tour-sketches/">&lt;!-- &lt;a href=&quot;{{ site.url }}{{ page.url }}&quot;&gt;absolute links&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;![Welcome](Tour_Welcome 1.png)&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One of the things that came up during &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;blogs.gnome.org&#x2F;shell-dev&#x2F;2021&#x2F;02&#x2F;15&#x2F;shell-ux-changes-the-research&#x2F;&quot;&gt;user testing&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; GNOME 40 was that people went through the &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gitlab.gnome.org&#x2F;GNOME&#x2F;gnome-tour&quot;&gt;Tour&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; and all the abstract(ish) UI illustrations didn&#x27;t really help people orient themselves on screen. We did get positive feedback on the feel of the tour though. For the new Tour &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gitlab.gnome.org&#x2F;Teams&#x2F;Design&#x2F;os-mockups&#x2F;-&#x2F;issues&#x2F;79&quot;&gt;we iterated&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; on some illustrations that help solidify &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;gitlab.gnome.org&#x2F;Teams&#x2F;Design&#x2F;app-illustrations&quot;&gt;the style&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; and give a nice welcoming vibe to the experience.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;inlineimgs&quot;&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Arrange_Yourself.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Arrange_Yourself.png&quot; alt=&quot;Arrange&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Overview.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Overview.png&quot; alt=&quot;Overview&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Workspaces.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Workspaces.png&quot; alt=&quot;Workspaces&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Up_And_Down_For_Overview.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Up_And_Down_For_Overview.png&quot; alt=&quot;Touch&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Because you can soon experience GNOME 40 yourself, here&#x27;s a few sketches of the exploratory phase. Be sure to check out some background on how the &lt;a href=&quot;&#x2F;posts&#x2F;animated-tour&#x2F;&quot;&gt;animations were done&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;blog.jimmac.eu&#x2F;posts&#x2F;tour-sketches&#x2F;Tour%EF%80%A2_Press_Super.png&quot; alt=&quot;Press Super&quot; &#x2F;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;inlineimgs&quot;&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Welcome.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Welcome.png&quot; alt=&quot;Welcome&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Overview.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Overview.png&quot; alt=&quot;Overview 2&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;TourWorkspaces.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Workspaces.png&quot; alt=&quot;Workspaces 2&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;Tour_Workspaces.png&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;Tour_Workspaces.png&quot; alt=&quot;Workspaces&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;
